journald-archive (0.3.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Use a POSIX sh shebang (#!/bin/sh) for the scripts that do not need bash:
    the four Debian maintainer scripts (postinst, postrm, prerm, config) and
    the journalctl-all wrapper. None used bash-specific syntax. The wrapper
    also drops its no-op `set -o pipefail` (it runs no pipelines), keeping
    `set -eu`. No bash dependency is added: bash is Essential, and the only
    script that still needs it — the private timer helper, which relies on
    process substitution and NUL-delimited `read -d` — keeps its bash shebang.

 -- Alexander <alexander.s.m@gmail.com>  Mon, 08 Jun 2026 12:24:12 +0000

journald-archive (0.3.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix journalctl-all failing with "No journal files were opened due to
    insufficient permissions" for non-root users in adm/wheel. The mergerfs
    union did not propagate the POSIX ACLs systemd-journald sets on journal
    files, so the kernel saw only the bare 0640 root:systemd-journal mode and
    denied access — even though the same files were readable directly on the hot
    tier. Mount the combined view with posix_acl=true so ACLs are honoured.
  * Remount the combined union on package upgrade. It was installed with
    --no-restart-on-upgrade, so mount-option changes (like the posix_acl fix
    above) would not have taken effect until a reboot. The union is a stateless
    read-only view, so remounting it is safe; the btrfs archive mount stays
    --no-restart-on-upgrade as remounting that loopback mid-operation is not.

 -- Alexander <alexander.s.m@gmail.com>  Mon, 08 Jun 2026 01:08:45 +0000

journald-archive (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Retention is now governed by physical disk space instead of a logical
    journalctl --vacuum-size cap. The archive keeps as much history as fits in
    its loopback file, so the actual btrfs compression ratio is discovered and
    used automatically rather than guessed at install time (the old 5x
    assumption both wasted space when compression was better and, when it was
    worse, could stall archiving entirely).
  * Eviction deletes the oldest archived journals until FREE_MARGIN_MIB of free
    space is restored. Free space is re-read after each delete with a
    `btrfs filesystem sync` in between, because btrfs frees extents only on
    transaction commit and the lagging counter would otherwise cause
    over-eviction (st_blocks/du report uncompressed size on btrfs, so we cannot
    account for freed space ourselves).
  * Add the FREE_MARGIN_MIB knob (default ~1/16 of the archive, capped at half
    the archive). Drop VACUUM_SIZE_GIB and its debconf question; the install
    now asks only for the single disk-budget number (the loopback size).
  * On upgrade, comment out the now-unused VACUUM_SIZE_GIB in existing configs
    and append FREE_MARGIN_MIB with a sensible default, without touching other
    values.
  * Archiving no longer leaves a truncated journal behind when a move fails
    (e.g. ENOSPC): the partial copy is cleaned up and the move retried next run.
  * Fix the helper being installed non-executable. Since 0.2.1 moved it under
    /usr/lib, dh_fixperms left it mode 0644 and the service could not run it;
    restore the executable bit in debian/rules.

 -- Alexander <alexander.s.m@gmail.com>  Sun, 07 Jun 2026 19:24:23 +0000

journald-archive (0.2.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Drop the redundant manual debconf dependency; it is already pulled in via
    ${misc:Depends} as "debconf (>= 0.5) | debconf-2.0".
  * Move the timer helper out of $PATH: install it to
    /usr/lib/journald-archive/ instead of /usr/sbin. It is a private helper
    invoked by the service, not a user command.
  * Make the archive grace period configurable via GRACE_MINUTES in
    /etc/default/journald-archive. It defaults to 30, matching the timer
    interval, so a rotated file is archived only after surviving a full cycle
    (the previous hardcoded threshold was 1 minute). Candidate selection now
    uses a single name/path/age-filtered find. On upgrade, configs predating
    the option get GRACE_MINUTES appended (without touching existing values)
    so the knob is discoverable.

 -- Alexander <alexander.s.m@gmail.com>  Sun, 07 Jun 2026 18:17:18 +0000

journald-archive (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add journalctl-all: a wrapper that queries the combined live+archive
    view (/var/log/journal_combined), with bash and zsh completion that
    mirror journalctl's.
  * Ship a journalctl-all(1) manual page.
  * Validate the debconf size answers; re-prompt on non-numeric input
    instead of failing configuration with a cryptic fallocate error.

